<!-- SECTION 1: STRATEGY OVERVIEW                -->
<!-- =========================================== -->
<div class="section" id="s01">
  <div class="section-label">01 / Strategy Overview</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">The Full Funnel: Cold to Platinum</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Organic and paid are not separate strategies. They feed the same funnel. Organic proves which hooks and magnets convert. Paid amplifies the winners. Both channels deliver leads into the same email nurture and setter pipeline. The only difference is the entry point.</p>

  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--orange);">
    <div class="card-title">Funnel Architecture</div>
    <div class="flow">
      <div class="flow-step" style="border-top:3px solid var(--purple);">
        <div class="flow-step-label" style="color:var(--purple);">Step 1: Cold Audience</div>
        <div style="color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:12.5px;">The Strategic Wealth Builder: 35-49 core (50+ larger assets), $1M+ net worth, $50K-$500K in crypto already. Business owners, senior professionals, real estate developers. North America (primary target for new acquisition) | Australia (existing member base, secondary) | UK/Europe (emerging). Reached via Hammer Them content ads (paid) or organic Reels/YouTube (organic).</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">&#8595;</div>
      <div class="flow-step" style="border-top:3px solid var(--orange);">
        <div class="flow-step-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Step 2: TOF Ad or Organic Reel</div>
        <div style="color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:12.5px;"><strong>Organic:</strong> Ben publishes IG Reel with Hand Raiser CTA. "Comment [KEYWORD] and I will DM you the link." <strong>Paid:</strong> Meta lead gen ad drives to landing page with email capture and lead magnet download.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">&#8595;</div>
      <div class="flow-step" style="border-top:3px solid var(--green);">
        <div class="flow-step-label" style="color:var(--green);">Step 3: Lead Magnet Delivery</div>
        <div style="color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:12.5px;"><strong>Organic:</strong> ManyChat DM delivers link within 60 seconds. <strong>Paid:</strong> Landing page instant download + email confirmation. Both qualify: tools ask about portfolio size, goals, risk. The lead magnet diagnoses. It does not prescribe.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">&#8595;</div>
      <div class="flow-step" style="border-top:3px solid var(--blue);">
        <div class="flow-step-label" style="color:var(--blue);">Step 4: 14-Day Email Nurture</div>
        <div style="color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:12.5px;">Customer.io sequence: 9 emails over 14 days. Delivers value, builds trust, handles objections. Every email reinforces the gap between what the lead magnet showed and what Platinum solves. Soft CTA on Day 13. Hard CTA on Day 14.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">&#8595;</div>
      <div class="flow-step" style="border-top:3px solid var(--orange);">
        <div class="flow-step-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Step 5: Setter Call</div>
        <div style="color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:12.5px;">15-20 min qualification call. Setter has full context: which lead magnet, what result, email engagement signals. Confirms fit, budget awareness, intent. If qualified, books closer call.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">&#8595;</div>
      <div class="flow-step" style="border-top:3px solid var(--green);background:rgba(5,158,120,0.04);">
        <div class="flow-step-label" style="color:var(--green);">Step 6: Closer &#8594; Platinum $14,999</div>
        <div style="color:#fff;font-weight:600;font-size:12.5px;">30-45 min strategy session. Deep portfolio review. Personalised recommendations. The close. Target: 25-35% close rate. Revenue per close: $14,999.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Key principle:</strong> Lead magnets are qualification tools, not just list builders. Every question the tool asks, every metric it surfaces, and every word in the copy is designed to attract people who can afford $14,999 and repel people who cannot. A lead magnet that generates 500 unqualified leads is worse than one that generates 50 HNW investors who match the ICP. Engineering the offer means embedding qualification into the hook, the copy, and the tool itself.
  </div>

  <!-- ICP PROFILE - Real Data (Feb 2026 survey + Jan 2026 sales calls) -->
