  <!-- TITLE VARIATIONS - SCORED FOR NA MARKET -->
  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--purple);margin-top:24px;">
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <span style="font-size:22px;">&#127482;&#127480;</span>
      <div class="card-title" style="margin-bottom:0;font-size:16px;">Title Variations &mdash; Scored for NA Market</div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:20px;line-height:1.7;">Strategic naming analysis for the North American HNW ICP (35&ndash;60, $500K+ investable, self-directed investors in property/stocks who are crypto-curious). Each title scored 1&ndash;10 for NA resonance. Updated 4 April 2026.</p>

    <!-- Ben's 4 Original Titles -->
    <div style="font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--orange);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:12px;">Ben's 4 Original Titles &mdash; Scored</div>

    <div style="padding:12px 16px;background:rgba(5,158,120,0.06);border:1px solid rgba(5,158,120,0.20);border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:8px;">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">
        <span style="font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:800;color:var(--green);">8.5</span>
        <span style="font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;">The Wealth Builder's Private Crypto Allocation Blueprint</span>
        <span class="tag tag-green" style="margin-left:auto;">&#9733; BEN'S PICK</span>
      </div>
      <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.6;">"Wealth Builder" is an identity label that resonates with self-made HNW Americans. "Private" signals exclusivity. "Allocation" is the magic word &mdash; it's what their financial advisor says, not what Reddit says. Hits all four levers: identity + exclusivity + credibility + action.</div>
    </div>

    <div style="padding:12px 16px;background:var(--card-raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:8px;">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">
        <span style="font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:800;color:var(--text-muted);">7.5</span>
        <span style="font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;">The Private Wealth Crypto Allocation Framework</span>
      </div>
      <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.6;">"Private Wealth" is a known financial services term in NA &mdash; immediately signals "this is for people like me." "Framework" sounds advisory but reads slightly cold for a micro magnet. Feels like a bank white paper, not a personal tool. Tweak: add "(One-Page)" to signal instant usability.</div>
    </div>

    <div style="padding:12px 16px;background:var(--card-raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:8px;">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">
        <span style="font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:800;color:var(--text-muted);">7.0</span>
        <span style="font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;">The Private Digital Asset Allocation Blueprint</span>
      </div>
      <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.6;">"Private" and "Allocation" are the right words. "Digital Asset" is clean and non-threatening but almost too neutral &mdash; could mean NFTs or tokenized real estate. Doesn't signal crypto conviction. NA self-directed investors respond to specificity.</div>
    </div>

    <div style="padding:12px 16px;background:var(--card-raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:20px;">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">
        <span style="font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:800;color:var(--text-muted);">6.5</span>
        <span style="font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;">The Private Digital Asset Positioning Framework</span>
      </div>
      <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.6;">"Positioning" is smart (implies cycle timing) but ambiguous in NA &mdash; marketing positioning vs. portfolio positioning creates a split-second of confusion. Stacks three abstract nouns with no emotional hook. Needs a concrete subtitle to land.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- 10 New Title Variations -->
    <div style="font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--orange);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:12px;margin-top:24px;">10 New Title Variations &mdash; April 2026</div>

    <table style="font-size:12px;">
      <thead>
        <tr><th style="width:40px;">#</th><th>Title</th><th style="width:120px;">Direction</th><th>Why It Works for NA</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="font-weight:700;color:var(--orange);">1</td>
          <td style="font-weight:700;color:#fff;">The Crypto Wealth Blueprint</td>
          <td><span class="tag tag-orange">CRYPTO WEALTH</span></td>
