<!-- SECTION 3B: SPLIT TEST IDEAS                -->
<!-- =========================================== -->
<div class="section" id="s03b">
  <div class="section-label">04 / Split Test Ideas</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">3 Tests Per Lead Magnet, Ready to Run</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">For each of the 5 lead magnets: one ManyChat DM hook test, one paid ad angle test, and one landing page headline test. All copy is genuinely different, not reworded. Run each test with a minimum of 200 impressions per variant before calling a winner.</p>

  <!-- STRATEGY SPLIT TESTS -->
  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--orange);margin-bottom:20px;">
    <div class="card-title"><span class="tag tag-orange">STRATEGY</span> &nbsp;Split Tests</div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:4px;">ManyChat Opening DM</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Direct Delivery</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, here is your Digital Asset Strategy Tool. It asks 5 quick questions about your situation then generates your personalised strategy. Takes about 3 minutes."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins on clarity. No friction, no tease. The person commented the keyword so they already want it. Just deliver.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Curiosity Gap</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, this is the same strategy tool our Platinum members use before they build their portfolios. Most people are surprised by what it recommends. Plug in your numbers and see."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: may drive higher completion rate by creating curiosity about what "surprised" means. Risk: feels less personal.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Paid Ad Angle</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Aspiration</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"I built a tool that creates your personalised digital asset strategy in 3 minutes. The same framework 3,000+ investors use to structure $500K-$5M+ portfolios."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins with warm audiences who already follow Ben. The aspirational "3,000+ investors" line creates social proof and draws in people who want to be in that group.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Problem Agitation</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"You have been thinking about digital assets for months. Maybe years. You have read the articles. Watched the videos. And you still do not have a plan. This tool changes that in 3 minutes."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins with cold audiences. Calls out the inaction pattern directly. More emotional. May outperform on CPL but could attract lower-intent leads.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Landing Page Headline</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Outcome-Led</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Get Your Personalised Digital Asset Strategy in 3 Minutes"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. Clear, specific, time-bound. HNW investors are busy. Telling them exactly what they get and how long it takes removes friction.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Authority-Led</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"The Strategy Framework 3,000+ Investors Use to Build Digital Asset Portfolios"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: may win if traffic is cold and needs trust before action. Social proof in the headline does the convincing. Risk: less clear on what you get.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SCORECARD SPLIT TESTS -->
  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--green);margin-bottom:20px;">
    <div class="card-title"><span class="tag tag-green">SCORECARD</span> &nbsp;Split Tests</div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:4px;">ManyChat Opening DM</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Score Anchor</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, here is your Wealth Protection Scorecard. 6 questions, about 2 minutes. The average score is 4.2 out of 10. Let me know what you get."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. The "4.2 out of 10" creates immediate curiosity. People want to beat the average. Drives completion rate.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Fear Framing</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, here is the scorecard. It will show you exactly where your portfolio is exposed. Most people are not prepared for what they find. 6 questions. 2 minutes."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: stronger emotional hook but may reduce completion if people feel anxiety about the result. Test against A to see if the fear framing lifts or suppresses action.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Paid Ad Angle</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Diagnostic</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Most HNW investors think their portfolio is protected from inflation. Most are wrong. Take this 2-minute scorecard and find out where you actually stand."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. Classic pattern interrupt. "Most are wrong" challenges their assumption. The diagnostic framing makes it feel safe (it is a test, not a pitch).</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Statistic Lead</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"We scored 3,000+ investor portfolios for inflation protection. The average was 4.2 out of 10. Where does yours sit? 2-minute assessment. Instant result."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: the specific number (4.2/10) may outperform the vaguer "most are wrong" on click-through. Adds credibility. Risk: less emotionally charged.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Landing Page Headline</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Challenge</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"How Protected Is Your Portfolio? Take the 2-Minute Scorecard."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. Direct challenge. Implies they might not know the answer. Short. Clean.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Shock Stat</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"The Average Investor Scores 4.2 Out of 10. What Will You Score?"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: the competitive angle ("I bet I score higher") may drive more completions. Risk: some people may be put off by the implication they will score badly.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CALCULATOR SPLIT TESTS -->
  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--purple);margin-bottom:20px;">
    <div class="card-title"><span class="tag tag-purple">CALCULATOR</span> &nbsp;Split Tests</div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:4px;">ManyChat Opening DM</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Speed Focus</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, here is the Allocation Calculator. Plug in your numbers and it will give you your recommended digital asset allocation in about 60 seconds."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. "60 seconds" is the strongest selling point. Fastest tool in the set. Speed = low commitment = higher completion.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Comparison Hook</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, here is the calculator. It will show you your recommended allocation AND how it compares to what institutional-grade portfolios look like. Most people are surprised by the gap."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: the "gap" framing may drive more curiosity and shareability. Risk: slightly longer, slightly more friction. Test whether the comparison angle outperforms pure speed.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Paid Ad Angle</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Question Hook</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"How much of your portfolio should be in digital assets? Not what the internet thinks. What the data says for YOUR situation. 60-second calculator. Plug in your numbers. Get your answer."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. The question is universal among HNW investors. "What the data says for YOUR situation" differentiates from generic advice. Direct and clear.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Underallocation Angle</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Most investors we work with are under-allocated to digital assets by 40% or more. Not because they do not believe in it. Because they have never had a framework. This calculator gives you the number in 60 seconds."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: the "40% under-allocated" stat creates urgency. Makes it feel like they are missing out. May drive higher CTR but could attract lower-quality leads motivated by FOMO.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Landing Page Headline</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Direct Answer</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Find Your Recommended Digital Asset Allocation in 60 Seconds"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. Clean. Specific. Exactly what the tool does. No ambiguity.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Self-Directed IRA Specific</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Self-Directed IRA Holders: Calculate Your Optimal Digital Asset Allocation"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: may win with a narrower, higher-intent audience. Self-Directed IRA holders are automatically HNW. Risk: excludes non-IRA investors. Run as a segment-specific variant.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- BLUEPRINT SPLIT TESTS -->
  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--blue);margin-bottom:20px;">
    <div class="card-title"><span class="tag tag-blue">BLUEPRINT</span> &nbsp;Split Tests</div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:4px;">ManyChat Opening DM</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Reference Frame</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, here is Ben's 1-Page Wealth Protection Blueprint. The 5-step framework our Platinum members use. Save it. It is designed to be a reference you keep coming back to."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. "Save it" implies lasting value. "Reference you keep coming back to" positions it as premium. Encourages download and retention.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Action Frame</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, this is the framework. One page. Five steps. Everything you need to stop researching and start building your digital asset portfolio. No fluff."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: "stop researching and start building" directly addresses the ICP pain of analysis paralysis. More action-oriented. May resonate with people who are frustrated with their own inaction.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Paid Ad Angle</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Anti-Information</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"You do not need more information about digital assets. You have read the articles. Watched the videos. And you still have not started. The problem is not information. It is framework. Here is ours. One page."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. Calls out the exact frustration of the ICP. "The problem is not information. It is framework." is a powerful reframe. Positions the blueprint as the solution to analysis paralysis.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Debasement Fear</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Your cash lost 18% of its purchasing power in the last 3 years. Property is stalling. Bonds pay less than inflation. The investors who are protecting their wealth right now are using a framework most people have never seen. 1-page blueprint. Free."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: the inflation/debasement angle is the core pain bucket for BLUEPRINT. This version leads with the fear. May outperform in a high-inflation environment. Risk: could feel alarmist to sceptics.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Landing Page Headline</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Framework Promise</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"The 5-Step Framework for Building a Digital Asset Portfolio (1 Page)"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. "5-Step" is specific. "1 Page" is disarming. Signals this is not a 40-page ebook they will never read.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Wealth Protection</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"How 3,000+ Investors Protect Their Wealth From Inflation and Debasement"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: leads with the fear (inflation) and the proof (3,000+). May win with audiences who are more worried about losing wealth than gaining it. Risk: does not describe the deliverable clearly.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- TAX SPLIT TESTS -->
  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--red);margin-bottom:20px;">
    <div class="card-title"><span class="tag tag-red">TAX</span> &nbsp;Split Tests</div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:4px;">ManyChat Opening DM</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Education Frame</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, here is the Digital Asset Tax Guide. 1 page. Shows you the framework our members use. Self-Directed IRA, trust, LLC, individual. Which structure for which scenario. This is education, not advice."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. The "education, not advice" disclaimer builds trust with HNW investors who are cautious about unsolicited financial guidance. Professional tone.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Savings Hook</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Hey, here is the tax guide. One page. The difference between 47% tax on gains and 15% or less comes down to one structural decision. This shows you what that decision is."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: the specific numbers (47% vs 15%) create a concrete savings mental image. More emotionally compelling. Risk: may feel like it is promising specific tax outcomes.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Paid Ad Angle</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Member Contrast</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Most investors pay full tax on digital asset gains. Our members do not. Not because they are avoiding tax. Because they are structured properly from day one. Free 1-page framework."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. "Our members do not" is the strongest hook in the set. Creates an in-group/out-group dynamic. The clarification "not avoiding tax" pre-handles the objection.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - IRS Compliance</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"The IRS is paying more attention to digital assets than ever. New broker reporting rules are coming in 2026. If you hold Bitcoin, Ethereum, or any digital asset in the US, your tax structure matters more now than it did 12 months ago. Here is the 1-page guide."</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: regulatory fear is a strong motivator for HNW investors who have more to lose. May outperform around tax season or after IRS announcements. Risk: could feel alarmist and reduce trust.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px;margin-top:12px;">Landing Page Headline</div>
    <div class="split-test">
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--green);">Test A - Structure Decision</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"Self-Directed IRA, Trust, or Individual? The 1-Page Guide to Tax-Smart Digital Asset Structures in the US"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: wins. Names the exact three options the guide covers. HNW investors who have asked themselves this question will click. Pre-qualifies for sophistication.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="split-variant">
        <div class="split-label" style="color:var(--orange);">Test B - Savings Led</div>
        <div class="split-copy">"How US Investors Are Structuring Digital Assets for Long-Term Capital Gains Rates Instead of Ordinary Income"</div>
        <div class="split-hypothesis">Hypothesis: leads with the outcome (savings) rather than the process (structure). May drive higher CTR. Risk: feels like a promise. Needs disclaimer copy below the fold.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="divider">


<!-- =========================================== -->
<!-- SECTION 4: PAID TOF AD STRATEGY             -->
<!-- =========================================== -->
<div class="section" id="s04">
  <div class="section-label">05 / Paid TOF Ad Strategy</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Jeremy's Framework Applied to CS Lead Magnets</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Ad objective: lead generation, not awareness. Organic proves which hooks convert. Paid amplifies the winners. Never put paid behind a lead magnet that has not been tested organically first. The IG comment data tells you what the market wants. The paid budget tells the market to give you more of it.</p>

  <!-- 4 Ad Types -->
  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--orange);">
    <div class="card-title">4 Ad Types to Run</div>
  </div>

  <div class="ad-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--purple);">
    <div class="ad-card-title"><span class="tag tag-purple">Type 1</span> Video View Retargeting Ads</div>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td style="width:120px;"><strong>Objective</strong></td><td>Video Views / ThruPlay. Build warm audiences from cold traffic at scale. This is the "Hammer Them" layer.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Audience</strong></td><td>Cold: broad interests (personal finance, real estate investment, S&P 500, self-directed IRA, Bitcoin ETF). Then retarget 25%+ viewers into lead magnet ads.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Budget</strong></td><td>30% of total TOF ad spend. Target cost per ThruPlay: $0.25-$0.50.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Hook/Angle</strong></td><td>Ben's podcast clips, market commentary, Platinum member testimonials, educational clips on allocation and tax. Content only. No CTA. No pitch.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>CTA</strong></td><td>None. The goal is consumption, not clicks. These viewers become the warm audience for Type 2.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="ad-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--orange);">
    <div class="ad-card-title"><span class="tag tag-orange">Type 2</span> Lead Magnet Direct Ads</div>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td style="width:120px;"><strong>Objective</strong></td><td>Lead generation. Drive to lead magnet landing page with email capture. "Free: [Lead Magnet Name]".</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Audience</strong></td><td>Warm: 25%+ video viewers from Type 1, IG/FB engagers (30-day), email subscriber lookalike. Do NOT run to cold.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Budget</strong></td><td>40% of total TOF ad spend. Target CPL: under $30.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Hook/Angle</strong></td><td>Lead with the specific tool. "Get your personalised digital asset strategy in 3 minutes." "Find out your inflation protection score." Use the post variations from Section 2 as creative templates.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>CTA</strong></td><td>"Get Your Free [Strategy/Scorecard/Allocation/Blueprint/Tax Guide]" - one button, one page, one action.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="ad-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--green);">
    <div class="ad-card-title"><span class="tag tag-green">Type 3</span> Venus Fly Trap Sequence</div>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td style="width:120px;"><strong>Objective</strong></td><td>Warm cold audiences through a 3-video content sequence before pitching. V1 Educate, V2 Prove, V3 Trust, then DR (book a call).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Audience</strong></td><td>Cold: broad HNW interests. Sequence narrows: V1 viewers (25%+) see V2, V2 viewers see V3, V3 viewers see DR. 75-90% drop-off per step is normal.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Budget</strong></td><td>20% of total TOF ad spend. V1 gets the largest share (largest audience, cheapest views).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Hook/Angle</strong></td><td><strong>V1 (Educate):</strong> "Most HNW investors are missing a critical piece of their portfolio infrastructure. Here is what the top 1% are doing with digital assets." <strong>V2 (Prove):</strong> Member case study with specific results. <strong>V3 (Trust):</strong> Objection handling: risk, time, "I already own some Bitcoin." <strong>DR:</strong> "Book a portfolio review call."</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>CTA</strong></td><td>V1-V3: none (consumption only). DR: "Book Your Free Portfolio Review" or lead magnet landing page.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="ad-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--red);">
    <div class="ad-card-title"><span class="tag tag-red">Type 4</span> Lookalike Campaigns</div>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td style="width:120px;"><strong>Objective</strong></td><td>Find more people like existing Platinum members. Highest quality lead source. Proven 3-3.9x ROAS historically.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Audience</strong></td><td>1% Platinum Lookalike (US/Canada). This is the highest value audience. Secondary: 1% email subscriber lookalike, 1% setter call completer lookalike.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Budget</strong></td><td>10% of total TOF ad spend. Small budget but highest quality. Scale if ROAS holds above 2x.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Hook/Angle</strong></td><td>Same creative as Type 2 (lead magnet direct ads). The audience quality does the work. No need for different creative.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>CTA</strong></td><td>Same as Type 2: lead magnet landing page with email capture.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Targeting -->
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">Targeting Hierarchy</div>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Priority</th><th>Audience</th><th>Use For</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><span class="tag tag-green">Primary</span></td><td>US/Canada 1% Platinum Lookalike</td><td>Lead magnet direct ads + Lookalike campaigns. Proven: 3-3.9x ROAS.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><span class="tag tag-orange">Secondary</span></td><td>IG/FB engagers (30-day warm)</td><td>Lead magnet direct ads. Already engaged with Ben's content.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><span class="tag tag-purple">Cold</span></td><td>Interests: personal finance, real estate investment, S&P 500, self-directed IRA, Bitcoin ETF</td><td>Video View ads (Type 1) and Venus Fly Trap V1 only. Never send cold to lead magnet ads.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><span class="tag tag-red">Exclude</span></td><td>Existing Platinum members, existing email subscribers (optional)</td><td>Exclude from all acquisition campaigns. Do not pay to reach people you already have.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Budget Split -->
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">Recommended Budget Split</div>
    <div class="stats-bar">
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-label">Video Views (TOF Cold)</div>
        <div class="stat-value">30%</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-label">Lead Magnet Ads (Warm)</div>
        <div class="stat-value">40%</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-label">Venus Fly Trap</div>
        <div class="stat-value">20%</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-label">Testing New Creative</div>
        <div class="stat-value">10%</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Organic-first rule:</strong> Only put paid behind a lead magnet keyword that has proven organic traction. If SCORECARD gets 3x more organic comments than BLUEPRINT, spend on SCORECARD first. Data leads budget allocation. Kill at $50 spend if CPL is 3x target. Scale at $100 if CPL is at or below target.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="divider">


<!-- =========================================== -->
<!-- SECTION 5: EMAIL NURTURE SEQUENCE           -->
<!-- =========================================== -->
<div class="section" id="s05">
  <div class="section-label">06 / Email Nurture Sequence</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">14 Days, 9 Emails, One Destination</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">This sequence runs in Customer.io after someone downloads any lead magnet (organic via ManyChat email capture or paid via landing page). Every email adds value while increasing desire for the setter call. All in Ben's voice. No hype. No em dashes. Subject lines optimised for mobile (under 50 characters).</p>

  <!-- Day 1 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 1</span> Deliver + Welcome</div>
    <div class="email-subject">Your [lead magnet name] is ready</div>
    <div class="email-preview">Here is the download link plus one insight most people miss.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], thanks for grabbing the [lead magnet name]. Here is your link in case you need it again: [LINK]. One thing to pay attention to when you go through it: most investors focus on what to buy first. The data says the order of operations matters more. Structure, then allocation, then assets. Get that order wrong and you end up paying for it later in tax, timing, and missed compounding. More on that in my next email.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">Download Your [Lead Magnet]</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Day 2 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 2</span> Key Insight #1</div>
    <div class="email-subject">The order of operations most investors skip</div>
    <div class="email-preview">Structure before allocation. Here is why it matters.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], yesterday I mentioned the order of operations. Here is why it matters. Most investors pick their assets first, figure out the tax structure later, and never build a rebalancing framework at all. Our members do it in reverse: Step 1 is the structure (Self-Directed IRA, trust, LLC, or individual account). Step 2 is the allocation (what percentage of your total portfolio). Step 3 is the assets (BTC, ETH, selective alts). When you do it in this order, every decision that follows is simpler, cheaper, and more tax-efficient. The [lead magnet name] showed you one piece of this puzzle. The full framework has 8 steps.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">Watch the Full Framework (15 min)</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Day 3 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 3</span> Social Proof</div>
    <div class="email-subject">How James went from researching to structured</div>
    <div class="email-preview">A property investor's first 90 days with a real framework.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], James is a real estate investor from Dallas. When he joined Collective Shift he had been "thinking about digital assets" for 18 months. He had some Bitcoin he bought on a whim but no strategy, no structure, and no framework for when to add more or take profits. Within 90 days he had a proper allocation framework, a tax-optimised structure, and a plan he actually follows. His words: "I stopped guessing and started building." That is what the right infrastructure does. It turns "I should probably do something about this" into a system.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">See How Our Members Build Infrastructure</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Day 5 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 5</span> Education</div>
    <div class="email-subject">One concept that changed how I think about risk</div>
    <div class="email-preview">Most investors measure the wrong kind of risk.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], here is a concept most investors never consider: the risk of doing nothing. Everyone talks about the risk of buying digital assets. Few people talk about the risk of NOT having any exposure. Over the last 5 years, a portfolio with zero digital asset allocation underperformed a portfolio with even a 5% allocation by a significant margin. The risk is not just "what if it goes down." The risk is also "what if it keeps going up and I am not in it." I am not saying put everything into digital assets. I am saying that a 0% allocation is itself a bet. And the data says it is not a good one.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">Watch the Full Allocation Framework</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Day 7 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 7</span> Pattern Interrupt</div>
    <div class="email-subject">The question most investors never ask</div>
    <div class="email-preview">Everyone asks what to buy. Almost nobody asks this.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], everyone asks the same question: "What should I buy?" Bitcoin? Ethereum? Something else? But the question that actually determines your outcome is different: "What infrastructure do I need around my digital assets to protect and grow them?" Infrastructure means: a tax structure that does not eat your gains, a rebalancing framework so you do not panic sell, a portfolio allocation that fits your total net worth, and a plan for taking profits when the time is right. The asset selection is step 4 of 8. Most people start there. The investors who build real wealth start at step 1.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">See the Full 8-Step Framework</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Day 9 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 9</span> Market Timing Context</div>
    <div class="email-subject">Where we are in the cycle right now</div>
    <div class="email-preview">Context for investors thinking about their next move.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], I get asked about timing constantly. "Is now a good time?" Here is how I think about it: there is never a perfect time. There is only the right structure and the right framework. The investors who built wealth through the last cycle did not time the bottom perfectly. They had a systematic approach that told them when to add, when to hold, and when to take profits. The ones who lost money were the ones who bought on emotion and sold on fear. If you are waiting for the "right time," you are asking the wrong question. The right question is: "Do I have a system that works regardless of timing?" That is what we build for our members.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">Watch: How Our Framework Handles Market Cycles</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Day 11 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 11</span> Objection Handler</div>
    <div class="email-subject">The fear that stops most investors</div>
    <div class="email-preview">Addressing the biggest concern I hear every week.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], here is the biggest fear I hear from investors like you: "What if I invest and it drops 50%?" It is a fair concern. Digital assets are volatile. But here is what most people miss: a properly structured portfolio with a clear rebalancing framework actually benefits from volatility. When prices drop, the framework tells you what to do (hint: it is not panic sell). When prices rise, the framework tells you when to take profits. The fear is not about the asset class. The fear is about not having a plan for when things move. Our members have a plan. That is the difference between investing and gambling.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">See How Our Members Handle Volatility</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Day 13 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 13</span> Soft CTA</div>
    <div class="email-subject">A conversation about your portfolio</div>
    <div class="email-preview">30 minutes. Your situation. No pitch.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], over the past two weeks I have shared our framework, member stories, and the thinking behind how we approach digital assets. If any of it resonated, here is the natural next step: a 30-minute portfolio review call with our team. It is not a sales pitch. It is a diagnostic. We look at your current situation, your goals, and your existing portfolio and show you exactly where the gaps are. Some people walk away with a clear plan and handle it themselves. Some people decide they want our help implementing it. Either way, you leave with clarity. If that sounds useful, book a time below.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">Book Your Portfolio Review Call</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Day 14 -->
  <div class="email-card">
    <div class="email-meta"><span class="email-day-tag">Day 14</span> Hard CTA</div>
    <div class="email-subject">Last call on portfolio reviews this month</div>
    <div class="email-preview">Our team has limited spots. Here is your link.</div>
    <div class="email-body">
      Hey [first name], this is the last email in this series. Our team has a limited number of portfolio review spots each month and we are close to capacity for this round. If you have been thinking about getting a proper digital asset strategy in place, now is the time to lock in a call. 30 minutes. We review your situation and show you where the gaps are. No obligation. No pressure. Just clarity on your next move. After this month's spots fill, the next availability is 3-4 weeks out.
    </div>
    <a class="email-cta">Book Your Call Before Spots Fill</a>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="divider">


<!-- =========================================== -->
<!-- SECTION 6: METRICS AND TARGETS              -->
<!-- =========================================== -->
<div class="section" id="s06">
  <div class="section-label">07 / Metrics and Targets</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">KPIs Across the Full Funnel</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Track every stage. If aggregate looks fine but SCORECARD converts at 3x the rate of CALCULATOR, you need to see that and reallocate. Segment-level tracking per variant, not just totals.</p>

  <div class="card" style="border-top:3px solid var(--green);">
    <div class="card-title">Full Funnel KPI Table</div>
    <table class="kpi-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Target</th><th>Why It Matters</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Lead magnet opt-in rate</strong></td>
          <td class="target">40-60% of landing page visitors</td>
          <td>Below 40%: weak headline or wrong audience. Above 60%: you have product-market fit on the magnet.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>ManyChat DM open rate</strong></td>
          <td class="target">85%+</td>
          <td>DMs have 3-5x higher open rates than email. If below 85%, check delivery speed and message length.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Email open rate</strong></td>
          <td class="target">35-50%</td>
          <td>Subject lines + sender reputation. Below 35%: review subject lines, check spam scores.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Email to setter call conversion</strong></td>
          <td class="target">3-5%</td>
          <td>Of all email subscribers from lead magnets, 3-5% should book a setter call within 21 days.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Setter call show rate</strong></td>
          <td class="target">60-70%</td>
          <td>Confirmation page + SMS reminders + pre-call content. Below 60%: fix the confirmation page first.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Setter to closer conversion</strong></td>
          <td class="target">60-70%</td>
          <td>Of setter calls that show, 60-70% should be qualified and passed to closer.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Closer to Platinum conversion</strong></td>
          <td class="target">25-35%</td>
          <td>Of closer calls, 25-35% should convert. Below 25%: setter is passing unqualified leads.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Cost per lead (paid)</strong></td>
          <td class="target">&lt;$30</td>
          <td>All-in cost per lead magnet download from paid ads. Above $30: diagnose audience or creative.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Cost per setter call booked</strong></td>
          <td class="target">&lt;$300</td>
          <td>Blended across organic ($0) and paid. Pure paid target: $300-$500.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Cost per Platinum sale</strong></td>
          <td class="target">&lt;$2,000</td>
          <td>Blended acquisition cost. Against $14,999 price = 7.5x ROAS minimum. Extremely healthy.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">Per-Variant Tracking (Weekly)</div>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th style="text-align:center;color:var(--red);">EXIT</th><th style="text-align:center;color:var(--purple);">FILTER</th><th style="text-align:center;">CALCULATOR</th><th style="text-align:center;">COMPARE</th><th style="text-align:center;">INFLATION</th><th style="text-align:center;">STRATEGY</th><th style="text-align:center;">TAX</th><th style="text-align:center;">IRA</th><th style="text-align:center;">BRIEF</th><th style="text-align:center;">GPT</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Keyword comments</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>DM delivery rate</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Time to result</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Tool completion rate</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Paid landing page opt-in</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Email nurture open rate</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Setter calls booked</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Show rate</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Close rate</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Revenue attributed</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Cost per Platinum</strong></td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td><td style="text-align:center;">-</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--green);">Lead Indicators (Daily)</div>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Keyword comments per post</li>
        <li>ManyChat DM delivery success rate</li>
        <li>Tool/landing page link click rate</li>
        <li>Tool completion rate</li>
        <li>Email capture rate (paid path)</li>
        <li>Speed-to-lead (setter contact time)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--orange);">Lag Indicators (Weekly)</div>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Setter calls booked from lead magnet path</li>
        <li>Show rate by lead magnet source</li>
        <li>Close rate by lead magnet source</li>
        <li>Revenue attributed to each variant</li>
        <li>Cost per Platinum per variant</li>
        <li>Blended ROAS across organic + paid</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Decision rules:</strong> If a variant's calls booked rate is 2x+ higher than others, shift organic posting and ad spend toward that variant. If a variant's close rate is below 20%, investigate: wrong audience? Weak tool? Poor setter context? If cost per Platinum from a variant exceeds $3,500, pause and diagnose before scaling.
  </div>
</div>

